
[1]peculate

   PEC'ULATE, v.i. [L. peculatus, peculor, from peculium, private
   property, from pecus, cattle.]

   1. To defraud the public of money or goods entrusted to one's care, by
   appropriating the property to one's own use; to defraud by
   embezzlement.

   2. Among civilians, to steal.
